MENINGITIS, MENINGOCOCCAL - GHANA (03)
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Meningitis, meningococcal - Ghana 980123225953
Meningitis, meningococcal - Ghana (02) 980205100315
Date: Thu, 05 Feb 1998 19:11:41 -0800
From: Dr. Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on meningitis in Ghana were extracted from
the GIDEON software program:
12,510 cases of meningococcal meningitis were reported during 1983 to 1985;
5,279 during 1992 to 1994; 479 (41 fatal) in 1996.
18,551 cases (1,403 fatal) of meningitis were reported in 1997, and
ascribed to group A meningococcus. The outbreaks originated in Bawku East
and Bolgatanga Districts (Northern Region) and spread to Bawku West and
Kassena-Nankan Districts (Upper East Region), and Gushegu-Karaga, Tamale,
West Mamprusi and Yendi Districts (Northern Region).
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
